<doc id="1322100" wikidata="Q332900" url="?curid=1322100" title="Anchor portal">
<text>An anchor portal or H-frame tower is a structure supporting overhead power lines in a switchyard. Their static function is similar to a dead-end tower. Anchor portals are almost always steel-tube or steel-framework constructions.

